      "text": "A sophisticated synthesis might be described as the combination of many powerful elements, a collection of parts that form a meaningful whole. It might take the form of a vision or a plan but importantly, it recognises that context and voice has been taken into consideration. Instead of adopting existing programs, practices or processes, a community might instead ‘cherry-pick’ and adopt the parts from each that best align with their philosophy to form a unique program or process to suit their context. "
